bug.short_desc: Fedora Media Writer don't work with proxy on Win7 64 bits (time out)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1203435 screenshot of the bug on w7 64bits professional
Description of problem: The Fedora Media Writer don't work through proxy server on windows 7 64 bits. It don't read the system proxy settings.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 3.96.0
How reproducible: Every time
Steps to Reproduce: 1. open Fedora Media Writer 2. click on Fedora Workstation (or any other OS option) 3. wait forever to download, it will not.
Actual results: socket error message
Expected results: Download ISO image and write it to the usb stick
Additional info: I've used Windows 7 Professional 64 bits.
